de.oaam.model.oaam

Interface Architecture

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ElementA, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArchitectureImpl

    public interface Architecture
extends ElementA
    A representation of the model object 'Architecture'. Model root element. Only a single instance is allowed. The model content is grouped in sequentially dependent layers for different subdomains.

    The following features are supported:

    • Include
    • Library
    • Scenario
    • Systems
    • Function
    • Hardware
    • Anatomy
    • Capabilities
    • Restrictions
    • Mapping
    See Also:
    OaamPackage.getArchitecture()

    • Method Detail

      • getInclude

        org.eclipse.emf.common.util.EList<Architecture> getInclude()
        Returns the value of the 'Include' reference list. The list contents are of type Architecture. A reference to child architecture models. Elements of included models can be used in this model. Inclusion allows to build up architecuture models in multiple files. The idea is that this model completes the included model. The real model is this model plus all elements of the included models.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Include' reference list.
        See Also:
        OaamPackage.getArchitecture_Include()
